!! Backlinks

<$let refs={{{ [<currentTiddler>ns-backlinks[]] }}}>
<$list filter="[<refs>!is[blank]]" emptyMessage="<em>No tiddlers reference this one via the namespace resolver.</em>">
<$list filter="[enlist<refs>]">
* <$link to=<<currentTiddler>>/>
</$list>
</$list>
</$let>

!! Forward links (namespace-resolved)

<$let fwd={{{ [<currentTiddler>ns-forwardlinks[]] }}}>
<$list filter="[<fwd>!is[blank]]" emptyMessage="<em>This tiddler has no namespace-resolved references.</em>">
<$list filter="[enlist<fwd>]">
* <$link to=<<currentTiddler>>/>
</$list>
</$list>
</$let>

!! Pin `_latest` in this tiddler's `\context`

<$let
	raw-text={{{ [<currentTiddler>get[text]] }}}
	pinned-text={{{ [<currentTiddler>ns-pin-context[]] }}}
>
<$list filter="[<raw-text>!match<pinned-text>]" variable="_ignore" emptyMessage="<em>No `\context` pragma with drifting pseudos found.</em>">

The `\context` pragma in this tiddler contains a pseudo-segment
(e.g. `_latest`). Click to snapshot against its current resolution —
the pragma text is rewritten to the concrete value, freezing the
tiddler's references regardless of future version drift.

<$button>
Pin now
<$action-setfield $tiddler=<<currentTiddler>> text=<<pinned-text>>/>
</$button>

</$list>
</$let>
"},"$:/plugins/rimir/namespace/changelog":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/namespace/changelog","text":"|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.1.16 |2026-05-06 |Two relink-rewrite fixes for cascaded subtree renames. (1) ''Pre-rename wiki wrap'': during a relink-titles cascade, flibbles' bulkops calls `deleteTiddler(fromTitle)` immediately before the nested `relinkTiddler(fromTitle, toTitle)` — so the resolver can no longer reach the original target when our rule fires. We now wrap the wiki in a "fromTitle still exists" view for the //current// resolution check, mirroring the pre-rename state. (2) ''Same-segment-count preference'': renaming `a/b/c/d` → `a/f/c/d` (as part of an `a/b → a/f` cascade) from source `a/b/c` referencing `[[b/c/d]]` now produces `[[f/c/d]]` (3 segments preserved) instead of `[[d]]` (collapsing to shortest). The smart-shortening function tries the original ref's segment count first and only falls back to shorter forms when no same-length form resolves. CI test-edition gains the relink-titles plugin so the cascade is exercised end-to-end. 2 new specs (167 total). |
|0.1.15 |2026-05-06 |Relink ''smart shortening'' for `[[ref]]` rewrites. After deciding a short ref needs updating, the rule now tries each suffix of the new title (last 1 segment, last 2, …) against the post-rename simulation and uses the shortest one that resolves correctly from the source. Concrete: rename `a/b/c/d` → `a/b/c/e` from source `a/b/c` rewrites `[[d]]` to `[[e]]` (was `[[d|a/b/c/e]]`); subtree renames produce `[[ai/foo]]` rather than labeled-absolute pins; labeled forms `[[label|target]]` get a shortened target portion when one resolves. Falls back to the original label-preserving absolute pin only when no suffix shorter than the full title resolves. Also: refs whose target was the user-typed full title keep absolute form (no auto-shortening of `[[knowledge/llm/foo]]`). 1 new spec mirroring the user-reported `[[d]]` → `[[e]]` case (165 total). |
|0.1.14 |2026-05-06 |Relink integration for ''namespace-resolved'' `[[ref]]` references. New `relink-prettylink.js` (module-type=relinkwikitextrule) hooks into flibbles/relink so renaming a tiddler updates every short ref that namespace currently resolves to it — not just literal-title refs. For each `[[ref]]` in scanned tiddlers, the rule asks the resolver "what does this point to right now?", and if the answer is `fromTitle`, simulates a post-rename wiki to decide the rewrite: short refs that still resolve correctly stay untouched; otherwise the rule pins the target with `[[displayText|<absolute new title>]]` so the link survives any further movement of the source. Absolute literal refs `[[knowledge/llm/foo]]` rewrite cleanly to `[[knowledge/ai/foo]]`. Reads `\context` pragma and (with implicit-context flag) the `context` field on the source so context-resolved refs are detected. Works under cascading subtree renames (relink-titles): each per-child rename pins its references to absolute. 10 new specs covering literal / labeled / walk-up / context / self-prefix / batch / no-op cases (164 total). |
|0.1.13 |2026-05-06 |New ''self-prefix'' resolver stage (off by default, gated by `$:/config/rimir/namespace/self-prefix`). Inserted between Stage 6 (context) and Stage 8 (walk-up): tries `<sourceTitle>/<ref>` once. Lets a deep note like `knowledge/llm/vendor/deepseek/model/v4` resolve `[[yt/AIsearch/engineeringDSV4]]` to its descendant `…/v4/yt/AIsearch/engineeringDSV4` — walk-up never finds descendants, only ancestors. Adds `"self"` as a new resolver status (collapsed to `ns-resolved` in CSS). Settings tab adds the toggle. New flag participates in the existing change-listener so toggling takes effect without a server restart. 8 new specs covering on/off behavior, multi-segment descendant refs, fall-through to walk-up, Stage-1-literal precedence, Stage-6-context precedence, and `$:/`-source/$`:/`-ref handling (152 total). |
|0.1.12 |2026-05-05 |Prettylink: source-title operand now picks `<thisTiddler>` (set by `$transclude $tiddler=...` in TW 5.4.0+) with `<currentTiddler>` as fallback. Previously, wikitext rendered through a `$transclude` (with no surrounding `<$tiddler>` widget) had `currentTiddler` empty, which silently disabled walk-up and rendered every bare `[[ref]]` as ns-unresolved. New regression test (`test-walkup-rendering.js`) covers the transclude path. |
|0.1.11 |2026-05-05 |Resolver: multi-segment refs (containing `/`) now go through context + walk-up like bare refs. Previously a ref like `[[test/sum]]` from `knowledge/llm/test/ergo` was rendered as unresolved (grey/italic) even though navigation handled it via the host app's linkcatcher; both paths now agree. System-namespace refs (`$:/...`) still short-circuit. Two existing tests inverted; three positive tests added. |
|0.1.10 |2026-04-16 |Relink integration: `\context` pragma and `<$context prefix>` widget attribute are now updated automatically when a referenced tiddler is renamed (requires flibbles/relink). New `relink-pragma.js` (relinkwikitextrule) and whitelist config for the widget attribute. 6 new relink specs (138 total). |
|0.1.9 |2026-04-16 |Feature flags: walk-up, aliases, pseudo-expansion, and implicit context are now optional (all off by default). New `featureflags.js` library caches config reads. Settings tab gains four toggle checkboxes with disabled indicators on diagnostic sections. Startup listener gates cache invalidation per flag and triggers full index rebuild on config changes. 22 new feature-flag specs (132 total). Docs updated for explicit-first design. |
|0.1.8 |2026-04-15 |Plug the seams Jasmine couldn't reach: parser-rule AST tests (`$let __nsref__` regression-guard), `\context` pragma AST, `$context` widget variable scope, `ns-resolve` / `ns-resolve-class` filter ops including widget-variable-vs-field precedence (27 new specs → 109 total). Companion Playwright e2e spec covers DOM rendering, click navigation, and CSS class application across walk-up, alias, mount, `\context` pragma, `context` field, and `_latest` pseudo (10 specs in `tw-tests`). |
|0.1.7 |2026-04-15 |Comprehensive test suite (82 specs) covering the resolver pipeline, `_latest` pseudo + version ordering, aliases (exact + pattern + precedence + chained), mount points (longest-first), the indexer (forward + backlinks + re-index), and the pin-context filter (regression for the NS-tab bug). Aliases and mounts refactored to WeakMap-per-wiki caches so tests stay isolated. `invalidatePseudoCache()` handles wiki-less invalidation. Tests run in CI before the library/demo dispatch. |
|0.1.6 |2026-04-15 |Stage 6 + tooling: backlinks indexer scans every wikitext/markdown tiddler (regex over body, with source-tiddler context detected via `\context` pragma or `context:` field); exposes `ns-backlinks` and `ns-forwardlinks` filter operators and an ''NS'' tiddler-info tab. New `settings` plugin tab listing registered pseudos, aliases, and mount points. ''Pin `_latest`'' button on the NS tab — one-click snapshots a `\context` pragma's pseudos to their current values. Known limitations: namespace-aware transclusion and editor autocomplete are deferred; `relink`-plugin integration not yet namespace-aware. |
|0.1.5 |2026-04-15 |Stage 5: mount points. Tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/NamespaceMount` with `from` + `to` fields rewrite a logical prefix to a physical one (pure prefix match, longest-first). Applied between alias and pseudo expansion. New `mount` status. Examples tab gets a //Mount points// page plus a demo mount. |
|0.1.4 |2026-04-15 |Stage 4: named aliases. Exact (`$:/tags/NamespaceAlias` with `short` + `expands-to` fields) and pattern (`$:/tags/NamespacePatternAlias` with `pattern` + `replacement`). Applied before pseudo expansion; chained up to 3 hops. Literal-on-raw-ref still beats aliases. Examples tab includes a new //Aliases// page plus two demo alias tiddlers shipped in the plugin. |
|0.1.3 |2026-04-15 |Live examples shipped in the plugin (examples tab) with bundled demo data. Walk-up now allowed within `$:/` titles (stops at a 2-segment minimum) so shadow-tiddler demos can showcase it. |
|0.1.2 |2026-04-15 |Stage 3: declared context. `\context <prefix>` pragma, `<$context prefix="…">` widget, and `context:` field on the tiddler. All three set the `ns-context` variable; the resolver tries `<context>/REF` before walk-up. Pseudo-segments inside the context prefix are expanded too. |
|0.1.1 |2026-04-15 |Stage 2: pluggable pseudo-segment framework (module-type `rimir-ns-pseudo`); ships `_latest` (version-max). Per-(pseudo,prefix) cache with targeted invalidation on wiki change. |
|0.1.0 |2026-04-15 |Initial stage 1: walk-up resolver, replacement prettylink rule, unresolved styling. |
